WEBVTT

00:00.801 --> 00:03.371
Lemon, I cannot marry you.

00:03.404 --> 00:04.772
Not when a part of me
is in love with someone else.

00:04.805 --> 00:06.374
Last night, when George was
calling off the wedding,

00:06.407 --> 00:07.041
I was kind of having
sex with Wade.

00:07.075 --> 00:07.541
This doesn't mean anything.

00:07.575 --> 00:08.509
I don't really care.

00:08.542 --> 00:09.777
BRICK:
How are you?

00:09.810 --> 00:12.113
Determined to get a job,
move on with my life.

00:12.146 --> 00:14.082
There's a job opening here
if you want it.

00:14.115 --> 00:14.915
And what better way
to show the town of BlueBell

00:14.948 --> 00:16.384
that you are willing
to start over.

00:16.417 --> 00:18.086
I'm Ruby.
Why haven't
we met before?

00:18.119 --> 00:19.087
You know in high school,

00:19.120 --> 00:19.987
you had me wrapped
around your little finger.

00:20.020 --> 00:22.490
I decided to stick
around for a while.

00:22.523 --> 00:25.093
You don't know who you are
without Lemon.

00:25.126 --> 00:26.527
You're asking me
to date other people?

00:26.560 --> 00:29.230
One day, you will
be single and healed.

00:29.263 --> 00:29.763
And so will I.

00:34.568 --> 00:37.338
Nope.

00:37.371 --> 00:39.407
Nope?

00:39.440 --> 00:40.741
That is never
happening again.

00:40.774 --> 00:44.578
Never, never,
never, never.

00:44.612 --> 00:47.815
Wow, Doc, that's one more
"never" than yesterday.

00:47.848 --> 00:49.550
You must, uh, really
mean it this time.

00:49.583 --> 00:51.219
I do.

00:51.252 --> 00:53.287
You can't quit now,

00:53.321 --> 00:55.289
not when you're finally
getting the hang of it.

00:55.323 --> 00:57.291
I am not finally getting...

00:57.325 --> 00:58.559
(laughs)

00:58.592 --> 01:00.294
You know, never mind,
it doesn't matter,

01:00.328 --> 01:03.164
because that
is never happening again.

01:03.197 --> 01:04.165
Just help me find my pants.

01:04.197 --> 01:07.135
Uh, that pile.

01:08.869 --> 01:10.238
The...

01:10.271 --> 01:12.506
Ooh.

01:12.540 --> 01:14.475
Maybe you, uh,

01:14.508 --> 01:15.743
just need a soothing hug.

01:18.879 --> 01:20.248
Come on.

01:20.281 --> 01:23.184
Damn it.

01:23.217 --> 01:24.685
(knocking on door)
Wake up.

01:28.689 --> 01:30.591
(knocking)

01:30.624 --> 01:31.592
(Zoe gasps)

01:31.625 --> 01:32.760
Ow!

01:32.793 --> 01:35.796
Zoe?

01:35.829 --> 01:36.697
Is that you?

01:37.898 --> 01:40.834
Hey, Rose!

01:40.868 --> 01:42.470
What are you
doing up so early?

01:42.503 --> 01:44.305
Sleep in, why don't ya?

01:44.338 --> 01:45.306
You're a teenager.

01:45.339 --> 01:47.675
Where are your pants?

01:47.708 --> 01:50.278
Oh, nowhere.

01:50.311 --> 01:52.846
I was, uh, running.

01:52.880 --> 01:53.847
Pantless.

01:53.881 --> 01:55.649
In heels, it's a new thing.

01:55.683 --> 01:56.750
People are doing it.

01:56.784 --> 01:59.119
I'm a doctor,
have to keep up.

02:00.921 --> 02:03.191
Rose, look at me!

02:03.224 --> 02:04.292
Exercise is so important.

02:04.325 --> 02:06.527
Come inside.

02:06.560 --> 02:09.597
ROSE:
Okay, so you remember

02:09.630 --> 02:11.865
how I finally found
my niche in high school?

02:11.899 --> 02:13.167
Ironic Japanese anime girl?

02:13.201 --> 02:14.168
After that.

02:14.202 --> 02:15.203
Indie rock girl?

02:15.236 --> 02:16.504
Right.

02:16.537 --> 02:18.272
Well, guess who's going
to the Black Keys concert

02:18.306 --> 02:19.207
this weekend in Austin?

02:19.240 --> 02:20.874
You?

02:20.908 --> 02:22.543
Rose, that is so exciting!

02:22.576 --> 02:23.944
No, if it was me,

02:23.977 --> 02:26.947
I would've gone,
"Oh, my God, guess who's going

02:26.980 --> 02:28.316
"to the Black Keys concert
this weekend in Austin?"

02:28.349 --> 02:29.550
Like that.

02:29.583 --> 02:31.352
No, Sara Lynn Willoughby.

02:31.385 --> 02:33.654
And when she walks into school
on Monday wearing that T-shirt,

02:33.687 --> 02:36.224
I'll be back to eating lunch
at the table by the Dumpster.

02:36.257 --> 02:37.258
Please, you have to help me.

02:37.291 --> 02:39.293
Okay, how?

02:39.327 --> 02:40.761
