02:42.263 --> 02:45.799
Oh, man, you know
I totally would,

02:45.833 --> 02:47.701
if it weren't wrong
in every possible way.

02:47.735 --> 02:49.537
Don't try to copy
Sara Lynn Willoughby,

02:49.570 --> 02:51.272
that is the opposite
of "indie."

02:51.305 --> 02:54.275
Be Rose, the best you
that you can be.

02:54.308 --> 02:55.743
Like you with your
pantsless running?

02:55.776 --> 02:58.178
There are health benefits, okay?

02:59.913 --> 03:01.949
MAGNOLIA:
 You're turning me into a liar.

03:01.982 --> 03:03.351
And how is that?

03:03.384 --> 03:04.485
People ask me,

03:04.518 --> 03:07.688
"Is your sister really a
waitress at the Rammer Jammer?"

03:07.721 --> 03:10.291
And I say no.

03:10.324 --> 03:11.659
Don't you ever think
about anyone but yourself?

03:11.692 --> 03:14.295
Magnolia Breeland, there is
no shame in honest work.

03:14.328 --> 03:15.829
I am an independent woman,

03:15.863 --> 03:18.299
working to save money to
move out of my father's house

03:18.332 --> 03:20.234
and into my own apartment.

03:20.268 --> 03:21.569
It's an inspiring
story actually.

03:21.602 --> 03:23.437
Hey, good morning, girls.

03:23.471 --> 03:24.572
Good morning.

03:24.605 --> 03:26.307
Daddy, please make
Lemon quit her job!

03:26.340 --> 03:29.843
Just give her money so our
family is not a laughingstock.

03:29.877 --> 03:31.345
Oh, no, no, no,
I have learned my lesson,

03:31.379 --> 03:32.980
I am not just
giving you girls money

03:33.013 --> 03:35.316
and smoothing your way anymore.

03:35.349 --> 03:38.419
It is not good for anyone.

03:38.452 --> 03:41.455
Oh, my God, see
what you've done?

03:41.489 --> 03:42.990
(groans)

03:43.023 --> 03:44.358
Thank you, Daddy.

03:44.392 --> 03:45.593
Not at all.

03:45.626 --> 03:46.860
Hey, you're doing
honest hard work.

03:46.894 --> 03:47.995
Good for you.

03:48.028 --> 03:50.564
You know, I just remembered.

03:50.598 --> 03:53.033
You know, with Addy enrolling
in graduate school in Mobile,

03:53.066 --> 03:54.902
I'm gonna be needing
a new receptionist.

03:54.935 --> 03:56.904
You know, that job,

03:56.937 --> 04:01.342
it's got medical benefits, and a
401K, and a nice, comfy chair...

04:01.375 --> 04:04.478
Thank you, but working for my
daddy is not that far removed

04:04.512 --> 04:05.679
from being taken care of
by my daddy, now is it?

04:05.713 --> 04:09.550
Oh, no, I was just thinking
about the wording for an ad.

04:09.583 --> 04:10.351
Mm-hmm.

04:16.524 --> 04:17.791
Thank you, ma'am.

04:17.825 --> 04:19.827
Hey, stranger.

04:19.860 --> 04:21.295
I haven't seen you all week.

04:21.329 --> 04:24.298
Well, yeah, you know,
it's a big town.

04:24.332 --> 04:26.767
Oh, yes, it's so big.

04:26.800 --> 04:29.069
So easy to hide in.

04:29.102 --> 04:32.506
Well, hey, hey, Lavon Hayes
hides from no one.

04:32.540 --> 04:34.842
You know, I've just been,
uh, busy running things.

04:34.875 --> 04:36.810
Oh, you've been running,
all right.

04:36.844 --> 04:38.379
But don't, okay?

04:38.412 --> 04:39.447
Nothing to be afraid of here.

04:41.749 --> 04:43.617
Hey, guys.

04:43.651 --> 04:45.619
Hey, Zoe.
Hey, guys.
Coffee?

04:45.653 --> 04:47.355
Hey, thanks so much
for the movie last night.

04:47.388 --> 04:48.356
So fun.

04:48.389 --> 04:49.623
Thank you.

04:49.657 --> 04:50.624
Lavon won't watch Kate
Hudson movies with me.

04:50.658 --> 04:54.094
